<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id628323f0-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1861"><num value="1861">§ 1861.</num><heading> Definition of tribally controlled postsecondary career and technical institution</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this subchapter, the term “tribally controlled postsecondary career and technical institution” has the meaning given the term in <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s2302">section 2302 of title 20</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id628323f1-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/471/tV/s501">Pub. L. 95–471, title V, § 501</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/110/315/tIX/s941/j/1">Pub. L. 110–315, title IX, § 941(j)(1)</ref>, <date date="2008-08-14">Aug. 14, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/3463">122 Stat. 3463</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
